{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01FTKEcVLJPvhJZPVyMN8q9n","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task complete. Here's what was wrong and what I did.\n\n## Root causes found\nThe snapshots were failing for three compounding reasons, not just missing credentials:\n1. **No `minio` Service existed** — so `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` didn't resolve. Elasticsearch's S3 client silently fell back to the real AWS endpoint, which is why the error was a misleading `InvalidAccessKeyId` (403 from AWS, not MinIO).\n2. **The `es-backups` bucket was never created** — the `minio-init` job had run before DNS was ready and failed.\n3. **The `es-secure-settings` secret did not exist**, and no S3 client/endpoint config was present anywhere.\n\n## What I configured\n- **Created the `minio` Service** (`port 9000 → app=minio`) so the documented endpoint resolves.\n- **Created the `es-backups` bucket** in MinIO (creds `minioadmin:minioadmin`, the only valid root credentials).\n- **Created the `es-secure-settings` Secret** holding `s3.client.default.access_key`/`secret_key`.\n- **Secure settings via the keystore**: added `s3.client.default.access_key` and `secret_key` to the Elasticsearch keystore on all 5 data nodes and called `_nodes/reload_secure_settings`. **Credentials are only in the keystore + Secret — not in `elasticsearch.yml` or env vars** (verified clean).\n- **Non-credential S3 client settings** (`endpoint`, `protocol: http`, `path_style_access: true`) added to the `es-config` and `es-config-new` ConfigMaps. A restart was required for these to take effect, so I did a rolling restart of the `es-cluster` and `es-data-new` StatefulSets.\n- **Registered `minio-repo`** (type `s3`, bucket `es-backups`); `_verify` succeeded on all 5 nodes.\n- **Created `snapshot-1`** → `state: SUCCESS`, 3/3 shards, 0 failures.\n\nOne caveat worth noting: the keystore entries were added at runtime and are not persisted across a future pod restart (the config dir is ephemeral). The durable backing exists in the `es-secure-settings` Secret; if you want them to survive restarts automatically, the next step would be an init-container that rebuilds the keystore from that Secret on startup."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":240,"cache_read_input_tokens":72576,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":240},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a6cb89a3-b47c-471d-8d0f-b2a2761001ee","uuid":"ecb1b720-8b6f-4393-b4b2-cdfcd028c905","request_id":"req_011CcAicD621CtycskLvHHAr"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":1180337,"duration_api_ms":435165,"ttft_ms":2657,"ttft_stream_ms":2628,"time_to_request_ms":409,"num_turns":41,"result":"Task complete. Here's what was wrong and what I did.\n\n## Root causes found\nThe snapshots were failing for three compounding reasons, not just missing credentials:\n1. **No `minio` Service existed** — so `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` didn't resolve. Elasticsearch's S3 client silently fell back to the real AWS endpoint, which is why the error was a misleading `InvalidAccessKeyId` (403 from AWS, not MinIO).\n2. **The `es-backups` bucket was never created** — the `minio-init` job had run before DNS was ready and failed.\n3. **The `es-secure-settings` secret did not exist**, and no S3 client/endpoint config was present anywhere.\n\n## What I configured\n- **Created the `minio` Service** (`port 9000 → app=minio`) so the documented endpoint resolves.\n- **Created the `es-backups` bucket** in MinIO (creds `minioadmin:minioadmin`, the only valid root credentials).\n- **Created the `es-secure-settings` Secret** holding `s3.client.default.access_key`/`secret_key`.\n- **Secure settings via the keystore**: added `s3.client.default.access_key` and `secret_key` to the Elasticsearch keystore on all 5 data nodes and called `_nodes/reload_secure_settings`. **Credentials are only in the keystore + Secret — not in `elasticsearch.yml` or env vars** (verified clean).\n- **Non-credential S3 client settings** (`endpoint`, `protocol: http`, `path_style_access: true`) added to the `es-config` and `es-config-new` ConfigMaps. A restart was required for these to take effect, so I did a rolling restart of the `es-cluster` and `es-data-new` StatefulSets.\n- **Registered `minio-repo`** (type `s3`, bucket `es-backups`); `_verify` succeeded on all 5 nodes.\n- **Created `snapshot-1`** → `state: SUCCESS`, 3/3 shards, 0 failures.\n\nOne caveat worth noting: the keystore entries were added at runtime and are not persisted across a future pod restart (the config dir is ephemeral). The durable backing exists in the `es-secure-settings` Secret; if you want them to survive restarts automatically, the next step would be an init-container that rebuilds the keystore from that Secret on startup.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a6cb89a3-b47c-471d-8d0f-b2a2761001ee","total_cost_usd":2.3213950000000003,"usage":{"input_tokens":4725,"cache_creation_input_tokens":57186,"cache_read_input_tokens":2100420,"output_tokens":26999,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":57186,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":800,"cache_read_input_tokens":72576,"cache_creation_input_tokens":240,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":240},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":640,"outputTokens":17,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.0007250000000000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-8":{"inputTokens":4725,"outputTokens":26999,"cacheReadInputTokens":2100420,"cacheCreationInputTokens":57186,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":2.3206700000000002,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"022d7f86-0ccd-4d70-b0be-dd152931b234"}
